<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Boston Scientific (BSX)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Boston Scientific using recently fetched financials and disclosed assumptions.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 20, 2026</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">
      {currentPrice ? `vs. market price of $${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} (${marginOfSafety}%)` : 'Market price unavailable'}
    </div>
    {currentPrice && (
      <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
        {verdictText}
      </div>
    )}
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(latestRev / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Latest Annual Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(latestFCF / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${eps[0] !== null ? eps[0].toFixed(2) : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate the intrinsic value based on math rather than comparables or market sentiment.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with base Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Boston Scientific generated <strong>${(latestFCF / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. We use this as the starting block (Year 0).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project Phase 1 Growth</h4>
      <p>We apply a mathematically derived Phase 1 growth rate of <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong> for the next 5 years, constrained by its historical revenue and FCF growth trajectory.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Terminal Value</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, cash flows are projected to grow perpetually at a mature terminal rate of <strong>{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>, closely tracking global GDP growth and long-term inflation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discounting (WACC)</h4>
      <p>We discount all future cash flows back to the present day using a <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</strong> discount rate, derived from the 10Y Treasury yield (4.18%) plus an equity risk premium adjusted for beta.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Equity Value per Share</h4>
      <p>Finally, we add net cash (or subtract net debt) and divide by the <strong>{latestShares} million</strong> outstanding shares to arrive at the intrinsic value per share.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Assumptions & Rationale</h2>
  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Phase 1)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Calculated dynamically. Derived from historical revenue growth ({ (historicalRevGrowth * 100).toFixed(1) }%) and historical FCF growth ({ (historicalFCFGrowth * 100).toFixed(1) }%), capped reasonably at 15% to maintain conservative estimates.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(2)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        The hurdle rate needed to justify owning the stock, calculated using a 4.18% 10Y Treasury risk-free rate, plus a standard equity risk premium of 5.5% adjusted for a beta of ~0.85 typical for large-cap medtech.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is around 3%. A conservative 3.5% ceiling ensures the company is not projected to outgrow the broader economy infinitely.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (Year 0)</td>
          <td>${latestFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h3>Terminal Value</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Component</th>
          <th>Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Year 6 FCF</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcfYear6).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${terminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
